# Intent

This repo exists to turn a Figma demo into a polished interactive frontend.

Prioritize:

- close Figma fidelity
- strong demo feel
- React + TypeScript implementation quality
- consistent visual taste

# Stack

- React 18
- TypeScript
- Vite
- current styling source of truth is `src/styles.css`
- preferred future direction for new UI work is Tailwind CSS, if introduced deliberately

# Rules

- Reuse existing page pieces and repeated UI patterns before creating new one-off structures.
- Keep `App.tsx` thin and place screen code in `src/pages/`.
- Use local skill files and repo rules for workflow and validation; do not encode large workflow instructions inside component files.
- Only create Code Connect mappings for stable reusable components, not for one-off demo screens.
- Use local state for demo navigation and interaction unless the project outgrows it.
- Do not invent backend logic.
- Add short `TODO` comments when real product logic is unclear.
- Preserve the same tone as the Figma design: soft depth, clean hierarchy, rounded surfaces, and mobile-first composition.
- Avoid generic design-system defaults that dilute the visual identity.
- If multiple screens share a stable pattern, extract a subcomponent.
- If multiple screens share the same content structure, move the editable content into a template/data module instead of duplicating JSX literals.
- Validate final spacing, typography scale, and tab/entry interactions against the Figma screenshot.

# Required Checks

- Run `npm run build` after meaningful changes.
- Make sure mobile frame layouts still render correctly.
